        {"question": "Why am I always tired no matter how much I sleep?", "answer": "The most common causes are: undiagnosed sleep apnea (80% of cases are undiagnosed), low ferritin without anemia (ferritin below 50 ng/mL), subclinical thyroid dysfunction (TSH above 2.5 with low free T3), and insulin resistance. Standard bloodwork typically misses all four. Request a comprehensive panel including ferritin, thyroid panel with free T3, fasting insulin, and consider a sleep study."},
